                                "stop": 13.339,
                                "byte_start": 89292,
                                "byte_stop": 142686,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has the announcement in 05-5224 Davis v. Washington, and 05-5705, Hammon v. Indiana."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 13.339,
                        "stop": 574.093,
                        "byte_start": 142686,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15049,
                            "name": "Antonin Scalia",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/antonin_scalia",
                            "last_name": "Scalia",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2693,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2693"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32678,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 58944,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/antonin_scalia_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10699,
                            "identifier": "antonin_scalia"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 13.339,
                                "stop": 17.409,
                                "byte_start": 142686,
                                "byte_stop": 158987,
                                "text": "It\u2019s me again."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.409,
                                "stop": 26.653,
                                "byte_start": 158987,
                                "byte_stop": 195976,
                                "text": "These cases are here on writs of certiorari to the Supreme Court of Washington and the Supreme Court of Indiana, respectively."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 26.653,
                                "stop": 47.661,
                                "byte_start": 195976,
                                "byte_stop": 279986,
                                "text": "The question before us in both cases is whether the admission of out-of-court statements violated the Sixth Amendment\u2019s Confrontation Clause, which states, \u201cIn all criminal prosecutions, the accused shall enjoy the right to be confronted with the witnesses against him,\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.661,
                                "stop": 52.139,
                                "byte_start": 279986,
                                "byte_stop": 297854,
                                "text": "The facts of each case described in brief are as follows."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.139,
                                "stop": 67.337,
                                "byte_start": 297854,
                                "byte_stop": 358667,
                                "text": "In the first of them, Davis, a 911 operator received a frantic call from Michelle McCottry, who was involved in an ongoing domestic disturbance with Davis, her former boyfriend."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.337,
                                "stop": 80.24,
                                "byte_start": 358667,
                                "byte_stop": 410285,
                                "text": "The operator asked McCottry a number of questions to determine what was happening and some questions about Davis to determine whether the dispatched police officers would be dealing with a dangerous felon."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.24,
                                "stop": 85.701,
                                "byte_start": 410285,
                                "byte_stop": 432123,
                                "text": "At some point during the 911 call, Davis apparently left McCottry\u2019s home."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.701,
                                "stop": 90.567,
                                "byte_start": 432123,
                                "byte_stop": 451663,
                                "text": "Police arrived on the scene within four minutes of the call."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 90.567,
                                "stop": 97.04,
                                "byte_start": 451663,
                                "byte_stop": 477472,
                                "text": "The State of Washington charged Davis with felony violation of a domestic no-contact order."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.04,
                                "stop": 107.225,
                                "byte_start": 477472,
                                "byte_stop": 518223,
                                "text": "At trial, only the police who arrived on the scene after Davis had left testified; McCottry herself did not."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 107.225,
                                "stop": 119.271,
                                "byte_start": 518223,
                                "byte_stop": 566392,
                                "text": "But the prosecutor offered a recording of the 911 call, which identified Davis as the assailant and which was admitted over Davis\u2019s Confrontation Clause objection."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.271,
                                "stop": 130.443,
                                "byte_start": 566392,
                                "byte_stop": 611114,
                                "text": "The jury convicted him, the Washington Court of Appeals affirmed, as did the Supreme Court of Washington, which held that McCottry\u2019s statements were nontestimonial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.443,
                                "stop": 138.527,
                                "byte_start": 611114,
                                "byte_stop": 643401,
                                "text": "In the other case, Hammon, a domestic disturbance call led police to the home of Hershel and Amy Hammon."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.527,
                                "stop": 141.644,
                                "byte_start": 643401,
                                "byte_stop": 655940,
                                "text": "They found Amy sitting on the front porch."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 141.644,
                                "stop": 148.675,
                                "byte_start": 655940,
                                "byte_stop": 684048,
                                "text": "She told them that nothing was wrong, but they asked for and received Amy\u2019s permission to enter the home."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.675,
                                "stop": 157.081,
                                "byte_start": 684048,
                                "byte_stop": 717694,
                                "text": "Inside, they observed a living room showing signs of an altercation, including a broken heater."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.081,
                                "stop": 161.442,
                                "byte_start": 717694,
                                "byte_stop": 735143,
                                "text": "Hershel, Amy\u2019s husband, was sitting alone in the kitchen."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 161.442,
                                "stop": 167.428,
                                "byte_start": 735143,
                                "byte_stop": 759072,
                                "text": "The officers asked him what had happened, he told them that he and his wife had had a disagreement, but that it never became physical."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.428,
                                "stop": 172.86,
                                "byte_start": 759072,
                                "byte_stop": 780805,
                                "text": "At some point, Amy came back inside and went into the living room."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.86,
                                "stop": 180.541,
                                "byte_start": 780805,
                                "byte_stop": 811525,
                                "text": "One of the officers stayed with Hershel in the kitchen while the other went to ask Amy about the night\u2019s events once more."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.541,
                                "stop": 204.024,
                                "byte_start": 811525,
                                "byte_stop": 905462,
                                "text": "This time, she described the altercation in some detail, saying that it began over a dispute about their daughter, that it evolved from being verbal to being physical, that Hershel started breaking things, that he threw her down, shoved her and punched her."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 204.024,
                                "stop": 218.146,
                                "byte_start": 905462,
                                "byte_stop": 961886,
                                "text": "After hearing her story, the officer asked her to write it out on a battery affidavit, a regular form that this police department had, and to sign that affidavit, which she did."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 218.146,
                                "stop": 221.958,
                                "byte_start": 961886,
                                "byte_stop": 977142,
                                "text": "The State of Indiana charged Hershel with domestic battery."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 221.958,
                                "stop": 225.554,
                                "byte_start": 977142,
                                "byte_stop": 991561,
                                "text": "Amy did not appear at the subsequent trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 225.554,
                                "stop": 240.958,
                                "byte_start": 991561,
                                "byte_stop": 1053210,
                                "text": "Although Hershel objected on Confrontation Clause grounds, Amy\u2019s statements about the events in question were admitted, both through the testimony of the officer who had questioned her and through the battery affidavit that she had signed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 240.958,
                                "stop": 243.203,
                                "byte_start": 1053210,
                                "byte_stop": 1062196,
                                "text": "Hershel was convicted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 243.203,
                                "stop": 247.453,
                                "byte_start": 1062196,
                                "byte_stop": 1079124,
                                "text": "The Indiana Court of Appeals affirmed, as did the Supreme Court of Indiana."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 247.453,
                                "stop": 255.292,
                                "byte_start": 1079124,
                                "byte_stop": 1110471,
                                "text": "It concluded that although the affidavit was testimonial and had been wrongly admitted, it was harmless beyond a reasonable doubt."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 255.292,
                                "stop": 266.378,
                                "byte_start": 1110471,
                                "byte_stop": 1154879,
                                "text": "The officer\u2019s testimony about Amy\u2019s oral statements to him, on the other hand, the Indiana Supreme Court held were not testimonial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 266.378,
                                "stop": 280.271,
                                "byte_start": 1154879,
                                "byte_stop": 1210468,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari in both cases, and in an opinion filed today with the Clerk, we affirm the judgment of the Supreme Court of Washington in Davis and reverse the judgment of the Supreme Court of Indiana in Hammon."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 280.271,
                                "stop": 304.465,
                                "byte_start": 1210468,
                                "byte_stop": 1307225,
                                "text": "In a 2004 case called Crawford versus Washington, we held that the Confrontation Clause bars the, \u201cadmission of testimonial statements of a witness who did not appear at trial unless he was unavailable to testify and the defendant had had a prior opportunity for cross-examination,\u201d which, of course, did not exist in either of these cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 304.465,
                                "stop": 314.014,
                                "byte_start": 1307225,
                                "byte_stop": 1345364,
                                "text": "We hold today, as we implied in Crawford, that the Confrontation Clause extends only to statements that are testimonial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 314.014,
                                "stop": 318.839,
                                "byte_start": 1345364,
                                "byte_stop": 1364694,
                                "text": "That is clear from the text of the Clause, which requires confrontation of witnesses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 318.839,
                                "stop": 321.998,
                                "byte_start": 1364694,
                                "byte_stop": 1377338,
                                "text": "\u201cWitnesses\u201d are those who bear testimony."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 321.998,
                                "stop": 333.686,
                                "byte_start": 1377338,
                                "byte_stop": 1424045,
                                "text": "None of the cases exemplifying the confrontation requirement at the time of the framing applied to nontestimonial hearsay, such as a victim\u2019s cries for help."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 333.686,
                                "stop": 348.195,
                                "byte_start": 1424045,
                                "byte_stop": 1482141,
                                "text": "To be sure, most of those early cases involved testimonial statements of the most formal sort, such as sworn testimony in prior judicial proceedings or formal dispositions under oath; but not all of them did."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 348.195,
                                "stop": 364.26,
                                "byte_start": 1482141,
                                "byte_stop": 1546402,
                                "text": "We do not think it conceivable that the Clause\u2019s protections can be evaded by having a policeman recite a defendant\u2019s unsworn testimony rather than the policeman\u2019s having the declarant sign a deposition to the same substantive effect."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 364.26,
                                "stop": 374.773,
                                "byte_start": 1546402,
                                "byte_stop": 1588407,
                                "text": "In Davis, therefore, we must ask whether objectively considered the interrogation that took place in the course of the 911 call produced testimonial statements."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 374.773,
                                "stop": 377.553,
                                "byte_start": 1588407,
                                "byte_stop": 1599588,
                                "text": "We conclude that it did not."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 377.553,
                                "stop": 386.15,
                                "byte_start": 1599588,
                                "byte_stop": 1633965,
                                "text": "911 calls are ordinarily designed to describe current circumstances that require immediate police assistance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 386.15,
                                "stop": 387.789,
                                "byte_start": 1633965,
                                "byte_stop": 1640548,
                                "text": "This case is no different."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 387.789,
                                "stop": 393.935,
                                "byte_start": 1640548,
                                "byte_stop": 1665103,
                                "text": "McCottry was trying to obtain help to meet an ongoing emergency; she was not acting as a witness."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 393.935,
                                "stop": 402.069,
                                "byte_start": 1665103,
                                "byte_stop": 1697599,
                                "text": "She was speaking in the present tense about events as they were actually happening, not reporting on events that were done."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 402.069,
                                "stop": 411.542,
                                "byte_start": 1697599,
                                "byte_stop": 1735529,
                                "text": "Objectively viewed, the primary purpose of the 911 operator\u2019s interrogation was to enable police assistance to meet the ongoing emergency."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 411.542,
                                "stop": 415.076,
                                "byte_start": 1735529,
                                "byte_stop": 1749635,
                                "text": "In Hammon, by contrast, the statements were testimonial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 415.076,
                                "stop": 420.994,
                                "byte_start": 1749635,
                                "byte_stop": 1773354,
                                "text": "In relevant respects, they were not much different from those that we held to be testimonial in Crawford."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 420.994,
                                "stop": 423.364,
                                "byte_start": 1773354,
                                "byte_stop": 1782758,
                                "text": "There was no ongoing emergency."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 423.364,
                                "stop": 432.076,
                                "byte_start": 1782758,
                                "byte_stop": 1817658,
                                "text": "The police quite properly conducted an investigation into whether, as they suspected, past events of a criminal nature had occurred."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 432.076,
                                "stop": 443.104,
                                "byte_start": 1817658,
                                "byte_stop": 1861752,
                                "text": "Such an investigation required them to ask Amy to tell them what had happened so that they could decide whether to arrest Hershel, not to end an emergency that was in progress."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 443.104,
                                "stop": 453.063,
                                "byte_start": 1861752,
                                "byte_stop": 1901563,
                                "text": "Objectively viewed, the primary, if not the sole, purpose of the interrogation in that case was to investigate a possible crime."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 453.063,
                                "stop": 464.989,
                                "byte_start": 1901563,
                                "byte_stop": 1949315,
                                "text": "From the perspective of the Sixth Amendment\u2019s text again, witnesses in court narrate and attest to the truth of past events, which is precisely what Amy Hammon did."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 464.989,
                                "stop": 481.955,
                                "byte_start": 1949315,
                                "byte_stop": 2017129,
                                "text": "To summarize our holdings in these cases, statements are nontestimonial when made in the course of police interrogation under circumstances objectively indicating that the primary purpose of the interrogation is to enable police assistance to meet an ongoing emergency."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 481.955,
                                "stop": 498.311,
                                "byte_start": 2017129,
                                "byte_stop": 2082539,
                                "text": "They are testimonial when the circumstances objectively indicate that there is no such ongoing emergency and that the primary purpose of the interrogation is to establish or prove past events potentially relevant to later criminal prosecution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 498.311,
                                "stop": 514.929,
                                "byte_start": 2082539,
                                "byte_stop": 2149099,
                                "text": "Finally, we again emphasize, as we did in Crawford, we will note that both of the abused spouses in these cases did not testify, which is not an unusual phenomenon."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 514.929,
                                "stop": 531.659,
                                "byte_start": 2149099,
                                "byte_stop": 2215973,
                                "text": "For that reason, we again emphasize, as we did in Crawford, that while the prosecution may not deprive a defendant of the right to confrontation, a defendant may forfeit that right; for example, by procuring or coercing the absence of a witness."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 531.659,
                                "stop": 541.47,
                                "byte_start": 2215973,
                                "byte_stop": 2255261,
                                "text": "The doctrine of forfeiture by wrongdoing is an established equitable principle necessary to allow courts to protect the integrity of their proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 541.47,
                                "stop": 553.055,
                                "byte_start": 2255261,
                                "byte_stop": 2301550,
                                "text": "On remand, the Indiana Courts may, if they are asked, determine whether a claim of forfeiture is properly raised and, if so, whether it is meritorious."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 553.055,
                                "stop": 567.123,
                                "byte_start": 2301550,
                                "byte_stop": 2357870,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Supreme Court of Washington is affirmed, the judgment of the Supreme Court of Indiana is reversed, and the latter case is remanded for proceeding not inconsistent with this opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 567.123,
                                "stop": 574.093,
                                "byte_start": 2357870,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment in Davis and dissenting in Hammon."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
